{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585316"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:08:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:08:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14954"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14954","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14954"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.74,0.06,0.03,0.17,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7642"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66449"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7642","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7642"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14954"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51900"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1063"},{"type":"tags","id":"2778"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"7943"},{"type":"tags","id":"8095"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18695"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18697"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66449"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old man presents with multiple hypopigmented patches on his arms and legs. He recently returned from working in rural India for two years. On examination, the patches are non-tender but have reduced sensation to light touch. A skin biopsy is performed.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following conditions is most likely to show granuloma formation on histological examination?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Leprosy","Staphylococcal abscess","Streptococcal cellulitis","Tinea corporis","Viral wart"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EGranulomas are organised collections of epithelioid macrophages that form in response to persistent antigens that cannot be easily eliminated. They are a characteristic feature of several infectious and non-infectious conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeprosy\u003C/strong\u003E, caused by \u003Cem\u003EMycobacterium leprae\u003C/em\u003E, is characterised by granulomatous inflammation affecting the skin and peripheral nerves. The presence of hypopigmented, anaesthetic patches in someone who has travelled to an endemic area is highly suggestive of leprosy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStaphylococcal abscess\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents as an acute, painful, fluctuant collection of pus without granuloma formation. The inflammatory response is predominantly neutrophilic rather than granulomatous.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStreptococcal cellulitis\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by acute inflammation with erythema, warmth, and tenderness, without granuloma formation. It typically responds rapidly to appropriate antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETinea corporis\u003C/strong\u003E is a superficial fungal infection that causes scaling and inflammation of the epidermis without granuloma formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EViral warts\u003C/strong\u003E are caused by human papillomavirus and result in epithelial proliferation rather than granuloma formation. They typically present as rough, hyperkeratotic papules.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther conditions that can cause granulomas include tuberculosis, sarcoidosis, and various deep fungal infections. The key to diagnosis is recognising the characteristic clinical features and obtaining appropriate tissue samples for histological examination when necessary.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Granulomatous inflammation is a characteristic host response to mycobacterial infections including tuberculosis and leprosy.","Leprosy classically presents with hypopigmented, anaesthetic skin patches or nodules.","Granulomas are organised collections of epithelioid macrophages formed in response to persistent antigens."],"references":["Sastry, A. S., \u0026 Bhat, S. (2018). Essentials of medical microbiology. JP Medical Ltd.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Borah Slater, K. A Current Perspective on Leprosy (Hansen\u2019s Disease). In: Christodoulides, M. (eds) Vaccines for Neglected Pathogens: Strategies, Achievements and Challenges. 2023. Springer, Cham. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-24355-4_3"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51900"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14954"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51900"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T09:40:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-30T09:41:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7642"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66449"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"me